#. Tag: title
#: docker_containers.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working with Containers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:10
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After you have created your images, you can start your containers based on "
"that image. You can run an instance of the image by using the "
"<command>docker run</command> command. The Docker engine then creates and "
"starts the container. The command <command>docker run</command> takes "
"several arguments:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:15
#, no-c-format
msgid "A container name - it is recommended to name your container."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specify a user to use in your container."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:25
#, no-c-format
msgid "Define a mount point."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specify a particular hostname, etc."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:35
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The container typically exits if its main process finishes. For example, if "
"your container starts a particular application, as soon as you quit the "
"application, the container exits. You can start the container again by "
"running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_containers.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "docker start -ai &lt;container name&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:39
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may need to remove unused containers, you can achieve this by using:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_containers.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "docker rm &lt;container name&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_containers.xml:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Linking Containers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:45
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Docker enables you to link containers together which allows for "
"communication between containers on the same host server. If you use the "
"standard networking model, you can link containers by using the <literal>--"
"link</literal> option when running containers:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "First create a container to link to:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_containers.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "docker run -d --name sles sles12 /bin/bash"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then create a container that will link to the <emphasis>sles</emphasis> "
"container:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_containers.xml:55
#, no-c-format
msgid "docker run --link sles:sles sles12 /bin/bash"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_containers.xml:56
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The container that links to <emphasis>sles</emphasis> has defined "
"environment variables that enable connecting to the linked container."
msgstr ""
